Text: COMP372 - Week 5 - 3/8 to 9/8.August 09, 2020.  .
3/8Continued working on tidying up the code and working on errors.
4/8Continued working on tidying up the code and working on errors.
Catchup with Teacher2 today.
Didn't realise that Toto hadn't been working on the project since he finished his API stuff ages ago.
Despite us having a list of user stories/tasks to get on with it seems like he finished his first one and then stopped.
The vitals user story was the next one and had just been sitting there till I asked him to start on it.
We haven't been very good at this whole Agile process.
I assumed we were all capable of more self-direction having sorted all the tasks/user stories at the start.
5/8Continued working on tidying up the code and working on errors.
had to organise with Toto how the vitals stuff was going to work as they only upload vitals if they are online and vitals are stored but for only a month.
6/8Worked on the display of the email today.

Had left it to Kiki to do for a few days but she has made no progress on it and has come up with a very complicated way to construct a complete HTML page rather than just a string with HTML tags built-in.
I am finding Kiki has not contributed much to this program at all.
Toto asked me to finish commenting my code which I will do and am happy to admit that not commenting as I go is probably my worst habit when coding.
7/8Lab this morning and meeting at Shift.
Toto asked again for me to comment my code.
I told him, like I told him last night I would I just hadn't had time since he asked and didn't think I would be able to get it all done today due to being quite busy.

He accused me of poor teamwork which is quite out of line since I have done the majority of the work on this project and I had already said I would comment my code but he seemed to ignore this and wanted it done on his schedule.
I understand my code should already be commented and I had already apologised for this.
I then dropped everything and left my lab early to comment the code.
We presented at Signal today.
Toto apologised lin the evening.
8/8Met with the team in-person to over the whole system and code together.
Toto turned up halfway through.
Didn't actually get much coding done as I had to help Kiki download some software to run the program and explain the program and very basic information to her.
Almost have the vitals call fully implemented.
9/8Decided I didn't think the program structure was right so did an overhaul to include more message queueing to decouple the different aspects of the program more.

Also got the vitals sending in an email but it is very difficult to test as it only works when devices become online again after disconnecting and we have no control over that so I had to mock up some arrays of devices and it appears to work.
Summary.

What have been the goals for the week and what did I achieve?Get deliverable handed to the clientTomorrow we meet so hopefully should be able to achieve this goal finallyStart work on next user stories - the reason for disconnection and email alert display.
Seems to be finished but hard to test fully given we have no control over devices.
